{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":884,"text":"So I'm an artist,"},{"time":2656,"text":"but a little bit of a peculiar one."},{"time":4386,"text":"I don't paint."},{"time":6434,"text":"I can't draw."},{"time":8153,"text":"My shop teacher in high school\nwrote that I was a menace"},{"time":12122,"text":"on my report card."},{"time":13953,"text":"You probably don't really\nwant to see my photographs."},{"time":17991,"text":"But there is one thing I know how to do:"},{"time":19980,"text":"I know how to program a computer."},{"time":21663,"text":"I can code."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22899,"text":"And people will tell me\nthat 100 years ago,"},{"time":26196,"text":"folks like me didn't exist,"},{"time":27570,"text":"that it was impossible,"},{"time":29684,"text":"that art made with data is a new thing,"},{"time":32658,"text":"it's a product of our age,"},{"time":34824,"text":"it's something that's really important"},{"time":36735,"text":"to think of as something\nthat's very \"now.\""},{"time":38837,"text":"And that's true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40029,"text":"But there is an art form\nthat's been around for a very long time"},{"time":44163,"text":"that's really about using information,"},{"time":46058,"text":"abstract information,"},{"time":48168,"text":"to make emotionally resonant pieces."},{"time":51080,"text":"And it's called music."},{"time":53632,"text":"We've been making music\nfor tens of thousands of years, right?"},{"time":57528,"text":"And if you think about what music is --"},{"time":59512,"text":"notes and chords and keys\nand harmonies and melodies --"},{"time":62360,"text":"these things are algorithms."},{"time":63790,"text":"These things are systems"},{"time":65641,"text":"that are designed to unfold over time,"},{"time":68049,"text":"to make us feel."},{"time":70195,"text":"I came to the arts through music."},{"time":71831,"text":"I was trained as a composer,"},{"time":73243,"text":"and about 15 years ago,\nI started making pieces"},{"time":76549,"text":"that were designed to look\nat the intersection"},{"time":79108,"text":"between sound and image,"},{"time":81036,"text":"to use an image to unveil\na musical structure"},{"time":83892,"text":"or to use a sound to show you\nsomething interesting"},{"time":86780,"text":"about something that's usually pictorial."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88804,"text":"So what you're seeing on the screen\nis literally being drawn"},{"time":92295,"text":"by the musical structure\nof the musicians onstage,"},{"time":95261,"text":"and there's no accident\nthat it looks like a plant,"},{"time":97817,"text":"because the underlying\nalgorithmic biology of the plant"},{"time":101180,"text":"is what informed the musical structure\nin the first place."},{"time":104515,"text":"So once you know how to do this,\nonce you know how to code with media,"},{"time":107943,"text":"you can do some pretty cool stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110055,"text":"This is a project I did\nfor the Sundance Film Festival."},{"time":113905,"text":"Really simple idea: you take\nevery Academy Award Best Picture,"},{"time":119178,"text":"you speed it up to one minute each"},{"time":121563,"text":"and string them all together."},{"time":123168,"text":"And so in 75 minutes, I can show you\nthe history of Hollywood cinema."},{"time":127592,"text":"And what it really shows you\nis the history of editing"},{"time":130595,"text":"in Hollywood cinema."},{"time":131800,"text":"So on the left, we've got Casablanca;\non the right, we've got Chicago."},{"time":135972,"text":"And you can see that Casablanca\nis a little easier to read."},{"time":138920,"text":"That's because the average length\nof a cinematic shot in the 1940s"},{"time":142276,"text":"was 26 seconds,"},{"time":143939,"text":"and now it's around six seconds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146999,"text":"This is a project that was inspired"},{"time":148767,"text":"by some work that was funded\nby the US Federal Government"},{"time":151735,"text":"in the early 2000s,"},{"time":152928,"text":"to look at video footage and find\na specific actor in any video."},{"time":159605,"text":"And so I repurposed this code\nto train a system on one person"},{"time":164305,"text":"in our culture who would never need\nto be surveilled in that manner,"},{"time":168176,"text":"which is Britney Spears."},{"time":169727,"text":"I downloaded 2,000 paparazzi\nphotos of Britney Spears"},{"time":173243,"text":"and trained my computer to find her face"},{"time":175743,"text":"and her face alone."},{"time":177148,"text":"I can run any footage of her through it\nand will center her eyes in the frame,"},{"time":181448,"text":"and this sort of is a little\ndouble commentary"},{"time":183648,"text":"about surveillance in our society."},{"time":185696,"text":"We are very fraught with anxiety\nabout being watched,"},{"time":188712,"text":"but then we obsess over celebrity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192219,"text":"What you're seeing on the screen here\nis a collaboration I did"},{"time":195973,"text":"with an artist named Li√°n Amaris."},{"time":198553,"text":"What she did is very simple\nto explain and describe,"},{"time":202451,"text":"but very hard to do."},{"time":203707,"text":"She took 72 minutes of activity,"},{"time":207208,"text":"getting ready for a night out on the town,"},{"time":209805,"text":"and stretched it over three days"},{"time":211918,"text":"and performed it on a traffic island\nin slow motion in New York City."},{"time":215949,"text":"I was there, too, with a film crew."},{"time":218192,"text":"We filmed the whole thing,"},{"time":219468,"text":"and then we reversed the process,\nspeeding it up to 72 minutes again,"},{"time":222893,"text":"so it looks like she's moving normally"},{"time":224811,"text":"and the whole world is flying by."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227091,"text":"At a certain point, I figured out"},{"time":229691,"text":"that what I was doing\nwas making portraits."},{"time":233500,"text":"When you think about portraiture,\nyou tend to think about stuff like this."},{"time":237086,"text":"The guy on the left\nis named Gilbert Stuart."},{"time":239173,"text":"He's sort of the first real portraitist\nof the United States."},{"time":242261,"text":"And on the right is his portrait\nof George Washington from 1796."},{"time":245510,"text":"This is the so-called Lansdowne portrait."},{"time":247732,"text":"And if you look at this painting,\nthere's a lot of symbolism, right?"},{"time":250996,"text":"We've got a rainbow out the window.\nWe've got a sword."},{"time":253680,"text":"We've got a quill on the desk."},{"time":255159,"text":"All of these things are meant to evoke"},{"time":257032,"text":"George Washington\nas the father of the nation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259832,"text":"This is my portrait of George Washington."},{"time":263776,"text":"And this is an eye chart,"},{"time":266809,"text":"only instead of letters, they're words."},{"time":269713,"text":"And what the words are is the 66 words"},{"time":272439,"text":"in George Washington's\nState of the Union addresses"},{"time":274923,"text":"that he uses more\nthan any other president."},{"time":278020,"text":"So \"gentlemen\" has its own symbolism\nand its own rhetoric."},{"time":282246,"text":"And it's really kind of significant\nthat that's the word he used the most."},{"time":286862,"text":"This is the eye chart for George W. Bush,"},{"time":289005,"text":"who was president when I made this piece."},{"time":292009,"text":"And how you get there,"},{"time":293201,"text":"from \"gentlemen\" to \"terror\"\nin 43 easy steps,"},{"time":296677,"text":"tells us a lot about American history,"},{"time":298761,"text":"and gives you a different insight"},{"time":300372,"text":"than you would have\nlooking at a series of paintings."},{"time":303333,"text":"These pieces provide a history lesson\nof the United States"},{"time":307291,"text":"through the political\nrhetoric of its leaders."},{"time":309571,"text":"Ronald Reagan spent a lot of time\ntalking about deficits."},{"time":313135,"text":"Bill Clinton spent a lot of time"},{"time":314724,"text":"talking about the century in which\nhe would no longer be president,"},{"time":318032,"text":"but maybe his wife would be."},{"time":321148,"text":"Lyndon Johnson was the first President"},{"time":323808,"text":"to give his State of the Union addresses\non prime-time television;"},{"time":327014,"text":"he began every paragraph\nwith the word \"tonight.\""},{"time":329378,"text":"And Richard Nixon,\nor more accurately, his speechwriter,"},{"time":332068,"text":"a guy named William Safire,"},{"time":333420,"text":"spent a lot of time\nthinking about language"},{"time":335492,"text":"and making sure that his boss\nportrayed a rhetoric of honesty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339449,"text":"This project is shown\nas a series of monolithic sculptures."},{"time":342375,"text":"It's an outdoor series of light boxes."},{"time":344847,"text":"And it's important to note\nthat they're to scale,"},{"time":347301,"text":"so if you stand 20 feet back and you can\nread between those two black lines,"},{"time":350939,"text":"you have 20/20 vision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352114,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":353176,"text":"This is a portrait.\nAnd there's a lot of these."},{"time":355505,"text":"There's a lot of ways\nto do this with data."},{"time":358791,"text":"I started looking for a way"},{"time":360435,"text":"to think about how I can do\na more democratic form of portraiture,"},{"time":365164,"text":"something that's more about\nmy country and how it works."},{"time":369419,"text":"Every 10 years, we make a census\nin the United States."},{"time":373244,"text":"We literally count people,"},{"time":375306,"text":"find out who lives where,\nwhat kind of jobs we've got,"},{"time":378474,"text":"the language we speak at home."},{"time":379975,"text":"And this is important stuff --\nreally important stuff."},{"time":382570,"text":"But it doesn't really tell us who we are."},{"time":384827,"text":"It doesn't tell us about our dreams\nand our aspirations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387522,"text":"And so in 2010, I decided\nto make my own census."},{"time":390936,"text":"And I started looking for a corpus of data"},{"time":394280,"text":"that had a lot of descriptions\nwritten by ordinary Americans."},{"time":397416,"text":"And it turns out"},{"time":398591,"text":"that there is such a corpus of data"},{"time":400357,"text":"that's just sitting there for the taking."},{"time":402365,"text":"It's called online dating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404574,"text":"So in 2010, I joined 21 different\nonline dating services,"},{"time":409544,"text":"as a gay man, a straight man,\na gay woman and a straight woman,"},{"time":412668,"text":"in every zip code in America"},{"time":414309,"text":"and downloaded about\n19 million people's dating profiles --"},{"time":417518,"text":"about 20 percent of the adult population\nof the United States."},{"time":421241,"text":"I have obsessive-compulsive disorder."},{"time":423084,"text":"This is going to become\nreally freaking obvious. Just go with me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426209,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":427375,"text":"So what I did was I sorted\nall this stuff by zip code."},{"time":431922,"text":"And I looked at word analysis."},{"time":433437,"text":"These are some dating profiles from 2010"},{"time":436134,"text":"with the word \"lonely\" highlighted."},{"time":438253,"text":"If you look at these things\ntopographically,"},{"time":441258,"text":"if you imagine dark colors to light colors\nare more use of the word,"},{"time":444782,"text":"you can see that Appalachia\nis a pretty lonely place."},{"time":449979,"text":"You can also see\nthat Nebraska ain't that funny."},{"time":456385,"text":"This is the kinky map,\nso what this is showing you"},{"time":462033,"text":"is that the women in Alaska\nneed to get together"},{"time":465160,"text":"with the men in southern New Mexico,"},{"time":466959,"text":"and have a good time."},{"time":468323,"text":"And I have this\nat a pretty granular level,"},{"time":471213,"text":"so I can tell you that the men\nin the eastern half of Long Island"},{"time":474344,"text":"are way more interested in being spanked"},{"time":476294,"text":"than men in the western half\nof Long Island."},{"time":479851,"text":"This will be your one takeaway\nfrom this whole conference."},{"time":482725,"text":"You're going to remember\nthat fact for, like, 30 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485489,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":488655,"text":"When you bring this down\nto a cartographic level,"},{"time":491102,"text":"you can make maps and do the same trick\nI was doing with the eye charts."},{"time":494580,"text":"You can replace the name\nof every city in the United States"},{"time":497421,"text":"with the word people use more\nin that city than anywhere else."},{"time":500437,"text":"If you've ever dated anyone\nfrom Seattle, this makes perfect sense."},{"time":503690,"text":"You've got \"pretty.\"\nYou've got \"heartbreak.\""},{"time":506416,"text":"You've got \"gig.\" You've got \"cigarette.\""},{"time":508855,"text":"They play in a band and they smoke."},{"time":511604,"text":"And right above that you can see \"email.\""},{"time":513612,"text":"That's Redmond, Washington,"},{"time":514942,"text":"which is the headquarters\nof the Microsoft Corporation."},{"time":517561,"text":"Some of these you can guess --\nso, Los Angeles is \"acting\""},{"time":520409,"text":"and San Francisco is \"gay.\""},{"time":522051,"text":"Some are a little bit more heartbreaking."},{"time":524067,"text":"In Baton Rouge, they talk\nabout being curvy;"},{"time":526172,"text":"downstream in New Orleans,\nthey still talk about the flood."},{"time":529083,"text":"Folks in the American capital\nwill say they're interesting."},{"time":531912,"text":"People in Baltimore, Maryland,\nwill say they're afraid."},{"time":534713,"text":"This is New Jersey."},{"time":536274,"text":"I grew up somewhere\nbetween \"annoying\" and \"cynical.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":538987,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":543250,"text":"And New York City's\nnumber one word is \"now,\""},{"time":545931,"text":"as in, \"Now I'm working as a waiter,\nbut actually I'm an actor.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":549201,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":550323,"text":"Or, \"Now I'm a professor of engineering\nat NYU, but actually I'm an artist.\""},{"time":554642,"text":"If you go upstate, you see \"dinosaur.\""},{"time":556591,"text":"That's Syracuse."},{"time":557766,"text":"The best place to eat\nin Syracuse, New York,"},{"time":559863,"text":"is a Hell's Angels barbecue joint\ncalled Dinosaur Barbecue."},{"time":562681,"text":"That's where you would\ntake somebody on a date."},{"time":564927,"text":"I live somewhere between \"unconditional\"\nand \"midsummer,\" in Midtown Manhattan."},{"time":568757,"text":"And this is gentrified North Brooklyn,"},{"time":570828,"text":"so you've got \"DJ\" and \"glamorous\"\nand \"hipsters\" and \"urbane.\""},{"time":574048,"text":"So that's maybe\na more democratic portrait."},{"time":576494,"text":"And the idea was, what if we made\nred-state and blue-state maps"},{"time":579587,"text":"based on what we want to do\non a Friday night?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":581780,"text":"This is a self-portrait."},{"time":583770,"text":"This is based on my email,"},{"time":585051,"text":"about 500,000 emails sent over 20 years."},{"time":588044,"text":"You can think of this\nas a quantified selfie."},{"time":591021,"text":"So what I'm doing is running\na physics equation"},{"time":594139,"text":"based on my personal data."},{"time":595561,"text":"You have to imagine everybody\nI've ever corresponded with."},{"time":598328,"text":"It started out in the middle\nand it exploded with a big bang."},{"time":601751,"text":"And everybody has gravity to one another,"},{"time":603953,"text":"gravity based on how much\nthey've been emailing,"},{"time":606238,"text":"who they've been emailing with."},{"time":607770,"text":"And it also does sentimental analysis,"},{"time":609626,"text":"so if I say \"I love you,\"\nyou're heavier to me."},{"time":611939,"text":"And you attract to my email\naddresses in the middle,"},{"time":614459,"text":"which act like mainline stars."},{"time":616578,"text":"And all the names are handwritten."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618917,"text":"Sometimes you do this data\nand this work with real-time data"},{"time":622649,"text":"to illuminate a specific problem\nin a specific city."},{"time":626071,"text":"This is a Walther PPK 9mm\nsemiautomatic handgun"},{"time":628771,"text":"that was used in a shooting\nin the French Quarter of New Orleans"},{"time":631826,"text":"about two years ago on Valentine's Day\nin an argument over parking."},{"time":635159,"text":"Those are my cigarettes."},{"time":636398,"text":"This is the house\nwhere the shooting took place."},{"time":638697,"text":"This project involved\na little bit of engineering."},{"time":641095,"text":"I've got a bike chain\nrigged up as a cam shaft,"},{"time":643334,"text":"with a computer driving it."},{"time":644674,"text":"That computer and the mechanism\nare buried in a box."},{"time":647464,"text":"The gun's on top welded to a steel plate."},{"time":649702,"text":"There's a wire going\nthrough to the trigger,"},{"time":652071,"text":"and the computer in the box is online."},{"time":654286,"text":"It's listening to the 911 feed\nof the New Orleans Police Department,"},{"time":657543,"text":"so that anytime there's a shooting\nreported in New Orleans,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":660444,"text":"(Gunshot sound)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":661469,"text":"the gun fires."},{"time":663300,"text":"Now, there's a blank,\nso there's no bullet."},{"time":666008,"text":"There's big light, big noise"},{"time":668106,"text":"and most importantly, there's a casing."},{"time":670452,"text":"There's about five shootings\na day in New Orleans,"},{"time":672872,"text":"so over the four months\nthis piece was installed,"},{"time":675237,"text":"the case filled up with bullets."},{"time":677642,"text":"You guys know what this is --\nyou call this \"data visualization.\""},{"time":682559,"text":"When you do it right, it's illuminating."},{"time":684591,"text":"When you do it wrong, it's anesthetizing."},{"time":687656,"text":"It reduces people to numbers."},{"time":689335,"text":"So watch out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692654,"text":"One last piece for you."},{"time":694466,"text":"I spent the last summer\nas the artist in residence"},{"time":697272,"text":"for Times Square."},{"time":698932,"text":"And Times Square in New York\nis literally the crossroads of the world."},{"time":702599,"text":"One of the things\npeople don't notice about it"},{"time":704800,"text":"is it's the most Instagrammed\nplace on Earth."},{"time":707903,"text":"About every five seconds,\nsomeone commits a selfie"},{"time":710809,"text":"in Times Square."},{"time":712424,"text":"That's 17,000 a day, and I have them all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715697,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":716806,"text":"These are some of them\nwith their eyes centered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719122,"text":"Every civilization,"},{"time":720183,"text":"will use the maximum level\nof technology available to make art."},{"time":723132,"text":"And it's the responsibility\nof the artist to ask questions"},{"time":725964,"text":"about what that technology means"},{"time":727619,"text":"and how it reflects our culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729662,"text":"So I leave you with this:\nwe're more than numbers."},{"time":732172,"text":"We're people, and we have\ndreams and ideas."},{"time":734197,"text":"And reducing us to statistics\nis something that's done"},{"time":737020,"text":"at our peril."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738295,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":739497,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}